article.headline: Va. Commonwealth 102, Houston 84
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Eric Maynor scored a career-high 28 points and B.A. Walker had 26 as Virginia Commonwealth cruised to a 102-84 win over Houston Saturday night. Houston (4-2) held the game close early on, leading by one with 13:36 left in the first half. But VCU (5-2) then broke it open, carrying the Rams to 49-27 lead at halftime. The Cougars outscored VCU in the second half, 57-53, and shot 58.3 percent, but that wasn't enough. The Rams also shot well in the second half, making 60 percent. Jesse Pellot-Rosa scored 20 and Michael Anderson 11 for VCU. Maynor also had a career-high 11 assists. Robert Lee led Houston with 21 points and Oliver Lafayette and Robert McKiver each had 15.
